      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To prevent cracks and bumps, use a properly sized setting-type compound for your first coat, making sure to feather the edges out widely. Apply your tape over the seam, pressing it firmly into the wet mud to ensure good adhesion. Subsequent coats should be sanded lightly and allowed to dry completely before applying the next layer, building up the mud gradually over several passes for a smooth finish.",
