    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "got it. one more thing—sometimes when i'm looking at older walls in houses i renovate, i'll see these tiny little holes or deep cracks that seem to go way back into the wall cavity. is that just rot or something? how do i fix those kinds of deep gaps without the whole thing falling apart?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Those deep cracks or holes could indicate structural issues, water damage, or just aging gypsum, and you must determine the cause first. If the drywall itself is compromised, carefully cut out the damaged section rather than just filling it. Replace the damaged section with new drywall, ensuring you connect it properly to the existing structure for a strong repair.",
      "source": "target",
